@node Story "Once upon a time..."
                       @{FG HIGHLIGHT}Bingo Bombgo, let the fun begin@{FG TEXT}
                      -===============================-

The eight Master Bombers ® have been assembled...

@{" Sherilyn Fenn   " Link Sherilyn}                          @{" Aththaathathatha " Link Mexican}
@{" Mitchell Sparks " Link Lifeguard}                          @{" Chief Gcaleka    " Link African}
@{" Don Rich Tea    " Link Gangster} - sorry, too much B5     @{" Rustam Shmarko   " Link Wizard}
@{" Kije Cho        " Link Ninja}                          @{" Vincent Collins  " Link Soldier}

...make your choice and prepare for a firey grave.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Allow me to disemminate...@{FG TEXT}
Once you know your @{"controls" Link controls}, kill your opponents by reducing them to highly
scattered unrelated molecules.  The complexity comes in the form of devious
tactics and the many ways in which to win.

Picking up @{"power ups" Link powerups} may give you that vital edge.

There are also other @{"gameplay options" Link gameopts} which you may use to configure the
game to suit your own particular taste.

The one player game is in a... how shall I put it... provisional state!  It
is just meant to act as a little training game.  You play against @{"Evil Joey" Link Joey}.
I suggest you go out and get some friends, or at least rent them for a
couple of hours, and play multiplayer.

The play area will be chosen at random from the home grounds of the
characters playing.  Depending on your chosen options, the native player
will be given an advantage.

What else is there to know.  Are you some kind of @{i}nutter@{ui}?

@{"I am a nutter" Link nutter}
@endnode
@node Installation
                            @{FG HIGHLIGHT}Installing B O M B@{FG TEXT}
                           -==================-

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}You will need:@{FG TEXT}
a) Not a lot.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}You will not need:@{FG TEXT}
a) Anything else.

Okay, you might need C:Installer and 1 MB CHIP RAM... yes, you'll
definitely need these.  But, nothing else.  I promise.

The game runs on an A600, and hence on the A500+, A1200 and A4000.  With
enough free chip ram, the globe will spin!  If there are any people with
½ MB chip + ½ MB fast (ie.  A3000s, newer A500s or expanded A2000s [or
A1000s for that matter!]) please @{"contact me" Link contacts} and tell me what happens, or
doesn't - what ever's the case.
@endnode
@node nutter "Everyone's a fruit and nut case"
                         @{FG HIGHLIGHT}Starting at the beginning...@{FG TEXT}
                        -============================-

The game was written in @{"AMOS Pro" Link Credits} for the @{i}Amiga Format write a game
competition@{ui}.  We like to make games which aren't just playable, but look
good too.  Why should a game have shoddy production just because it's PD?

Anyway, the character graphics were all drawn in @{"DPaint" Link Credits} (except for the
@{"Sherilyn Fenn" Link Sherilyn} close up) by @{"Alex" Link Alex}.  The spinning versus and globe anim were
rendered in the rendering tool of the gods - @{"Lightwave 3D v3.5" Link Credits}.

The music was written in @{"OctaMED v3" Link Credits} by @{"Jake" Link Jake}.

The actual executable (@{i}BOMBprogram@{ui}) is crunched with @{"CrunchMania" Link Credits}.  This is,
obviously, to fit everything on the disk.  

What do you want to know?  If there are any specifics you want to know
about, then please @{"contact me" Link contacts}.  I'd appreciate @{b}any@{ub} feedback.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Things @{"Jon" Link Jon} was "too busy" to do@{FG TEXT}

Occasional occurence of invisible blocks.  These can be blown up.
Some display bugs, eg. flames or half blocks left behind after an explosion.
Possible problem with shields and/or drawn games.
@endnode
@node controls "Mobility is hardly ever underrated"
The default controls are:

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Player 1@{FG TEXT}    S  Z  Left ALT  Left AMIGA  Left Shift
@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Player 2@{FG TEXT}    F10  =  P  [  Right Shift
@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Player 3@{FG TEXT}    Joystick 1 (game port)
@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Player 4@{FG TEXT}    Joystick 2 (mouse port)

There is now... @{b}four player joystick adaptor support@{ub}.  You'll need the
hardware, natch, but it's the standard one.  Change the default options in
the control options menu.

The keys are not my first choice as, if you have played,  you may have
guessed.  This is a system constraint set up by a combination of @{"AMOS" Link Credits} and
Commodore.  If any other combination is used the keys will jam, an paralyze
another player (grrr.).

@endnode
