@node History "In The Beginning"
                                 @{FG HIGHLIGHT}History@{FG TEXT}
                                -=======-

@{"Jon" Link Jon}, @{"Beej" Link Beej}, @{"Alex" Link Alex} and myself (@{"Matt" Link Matt}) all met at a boarding school and
quickly got to know each other through the mighty Amiga.  @{"Silicon Circus" Link Authors}
was originally @{"Jon" Link Jon} and @{"Beej" Link Beej}.  I was allowed to join, and although we had a
"group", we weren't actually doing anything.  Well, we saw @{"Alex" Link Alex} mucking
around on @{"DPaint" Link Credits} drawing an overhead man holding a gun, and decided the
time had come to make our first release.

So, @{"SC" Link Authors} (now numbering 4) got a-going.  I phoned @{"Jake" Link Jake}, who I already knew
could write music stupidly well, and then there were five.

We started off writing an @{i}Alien Breed@{ui} clone called @{i}Gangster@{ui}, using a
larger version of @{"Don Rich Tea" Link Gangster}.  We soon came across some limitations of
standard @{"Amos Pro" Link Credits}.  We switched to @{b}BOMB@{ub} which was our backup for a game
idea for the @{i}Amiga Format @{"Amos Pro" Link Credits} games competition@{ui}.  Avoiding starting
off a sentence with "We".  There we go.  Now that's two.  Now that's three.
Anyway, where was I?  Ah yes, well in AF75 we won the competition with
twelve others.  Hmph.  We were very pleased nonetheless.  The screen shot
in the mag was from v1.0 (not a good thing).  We did send them v1.1 as
well.  Now it's v1.2, which we hope will be on an AF coverdisk (magnetic or
compact).

Anyway, we hope you like the game.  I think it's the best bomberman game
for the Amiga, but then again I would, wouldn't I?  We'll probably end up
doing updates, but the next should be @{"Beware of Greeks" Link bog} - a graphical
adventure with a combined programming team of @{"Silicon Circus" Link Authors} and Visions of
the Impossible (who did the @{"Archimedes conversion" Link bombarch}) to make Silicon Visions
(provisional title).  The @{"PC version" Link bombpc} is on the way.

More about can be found out about these things @{"here" Link Contacts}.

Matt ;)
@endnode
