@node powerups "...and downs"
                                @{FG HIGHLIGHT}Power-ups@{FG TEXT}
                               -=========-

There are many different power-ups in @{b}BOMB@{ub} which can affect the players
abilities drastically. Some are vital to the way in which the game works,
others are just for added enjoyment.

@{"Let me peek at them through a key hole, Matt." System "C:Run >NIL: Multiview BOMB:PowerUps"}

Allow me to hand over to Jon and Beej, and a lesson in semantics.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Extra Bomb@{FG TEXT}
Gives the ability to lay an extra bomb concurrently for the remainder of
the round.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Fire Power@{FG TEXT}
Makes the length of the flame from your bombs one square longer for the
remainder of the round.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Detonate@{FG TEXT}
Sets off all bombs as soon as it is collected.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Random@{FG TEXT}
Randomly selects one of the other power-ups.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Reverse Control@{FG TEXT}
After collection, pressing 'Up' moves your player 'Down', and pressing
'Left' moves your player 'Right', etc. The fire button is not affected.
This lasts for a set period of time which is extended if further reverse
control power-ups are collected.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Shield@{FG TEXT}
Makes your player invulnerable to both bombs and the 'Death' power-up for a
set period of time.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Death@{FG TEXT}
Kills your player instantly, unless the shield power-up is still active.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Freeze Opponents@{FG TEXT}
Stops all other players at their current positions for a set period of
time, which is extended for longer if further freeze opponent power-ups are
collected.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Reveal Power-ups@{FG TEXT}
Removes the rubble from all squares which contain a power-up.  A second
reveal power-ups will have no effect.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Autolay@{FG TEXT}
When your player can lay a bomb (ie. when your player is not already on top
of a bomb, and your player still has bombs to be laid), the bomb is
automatically layed.  This continues until the end of the round, or until
you collect another autolay power-up.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Opponent slowdown@{FG TEXT}
All other players slow down to half their normal speed for a set period of
time.  This time is extended if you collect another opponent slowdown
power-up.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Slowdown@{FG TEXT}
Slows your player down to half of their normal speed for a set period of
time.  This time is extended if you collect further slowdown power-ups.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Diddy Bombs@{FG TEXT}
Immediately changes your player fire power to a length of one square, and
makes the number of bombs which you may concurrently lay one.  You may
collect further extra bomb or fire power power-ups to rebuild your arsenal.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Teleport@{FG TEXT}
Moves your player to a random empty square in the playing area straight
away.  When teleport mode is 'Shifting', the player will move towards the
selected empty square at their normal pace. 'Porting' mode will move the
player to the empty square immediately.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Slippy-Slidey (Ice World)@{FG TEXT}
Continues to attempt to move your player in the most recently selected
direction even if you have stopped your player. This lasts for a set period
of time which is extended if you collect further Slippy-slidey power-ups.
@endnode
