@node gameopts "Purple Alien Levels ! eek!(TM)"
                              @{FG HIGHLIGHT}Gameplay Options@{FG TEXT}
                             -================-

Several options which affect the gameplay have also been included in the
game. This generally changes the duration of specific power-ups, or deals
with other in-game parameters.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Bomb Type@{FG TEXT}
This is the way in which the bombs count down to zero. They can either be
represented by @{i}counting@{ui} bombs of the same size, or by @{i}swelling@{ui} bombs
which grow larger as the fuse time elapses, or as pulsating bombs which
swell the bombs in and out until they explode.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Bomb Timing@{FG TEXT}
The time it takes for the bomb to explode after being laid by a player can
be specified here.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Home Advantage@{FG TEXT}
Because every player in the game has a home ground, they all receive a
bonus power-up when they play on home soil. The home player may either
start with one extra bomb, a longer flame, or neither.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Stuart Campbell@{FG TEXT}
For those of you that do not know WHO this gentleman is, let US inform you
that DEAR Stu was big cheese at top English magazine @{b}AMIGA POWER@{ub}, until
he somehow found himself working for @{i}Sensible Software@{ui} in SAFFRON WALDON.
The git. But then, in a position MANY Amigans are envious of, he promptly
instigates one of the most foul software crimes of this century. Yes my
friends, Stuart is the man responsible for the PURPLE ALIEN LEVELS in
@{i}Cannon Fodder 2@{ui}. To REMIND you of this most heinous act, we give you THREE
LEVELS of CAMPBELLNESS - None, Purple, and Very Purple.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Link Side@{FG TEXT}
Used to select which of the two machines in a link game is which.
NB: This is ONLY used in the @{"registered" Link registration} version of the game.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Shield on Startup@{FG TEXT}
When selected, this option gives every player a shield of invulnerability
as soon as the game starts. This is to prevent those trigger-happy folk
dying a premature death. It will still run out after the defined time.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Shield Time@{FG TEXT}
You may set the duration of every shield here in seconds.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Freeze Time@{FG TEXT}
This defines the period of time in seconds for which players are frozen
whenever the 'Freeze Opponents' power-up is collected.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Speedup Time@{FG TEXT}
The time in seconds for which players are slowed down, whether
comparatively (opponents) or directly (yourself).

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Reverse Time@{FG TEXT}
Here the duration of the 'Reverse Controls' power-up can be set in seconds.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Exploding Death@{FG TEXT}
With this set, a bomb will explode the moment a player dies. With any luck,
the dying players may take other players with them !

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Teleport Mode@{FG TEXT}
The 'Teleport' power-up has two settings - on @{i}Shifting@{ui}, the teleporting
player will move horizontally and vertically across the game area until the
destination is reached. @{i}Porting@{ui} will cause the player to appear at the new
destination square immediately.

@{FG HIGHLIGHT}Slippy-slidey Time@{FG TEXT}
The time it takes until this power-up wears off can be set here in seconds.
@endnode
